Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with natural language processing techniques like distributional semantics and word embeddings to learn vector representations of fashion items. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper uses convolutional neural networks to learn the vector representations of fashion items, which is a common technique used in computer vision and pattern recognition. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a machine learning model for learning vector representations of fashion items. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with recommendation systems, which is a common application of information retrieval techniques. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with fashion items, which can be considered as a form of multimedia content.
